Saving & Shopping

   You know it's important to save money, but it's not always easy to
   stash any spare cash. Spending money wisely usually takes skill, time,
   and experience. This information can help you shop smart, save money,
   and learn how to spot, stop and avoid scams.

[15]Setting Out on Your Own

   Here's how to create a basic budget.

[16]Shopping Tips

   There's no shortage of ads from merchants who want your business;
   here's how to decide if the deal is for real.

[17]"Free" Trial Offers?

   Some companies use "free" trial offers as a lure, but don't make their
   cancellation policies obvious. The result? You could end up paying for
   a product every month, whether you like it or not.

[18]Using Money Transfer Services

   When and how to use a money transfer service safely.

[19]Scam Alerts

   Stay a step ahead with the latest info and practical tips from the
   nation's consume protection agency. Browse FTC scam alerts by topic or
   by most recent.

Credit & Debt

   Your credit report says a lot about you, and businesses use the
   information to evaluate your applications for credit, insurance,
   employment, or renting a place to live. Learn how to order copies of
   your free annual credit report, your rights and responsibilities when
   using credit, and options for dealing with debt.

[20]Free Credit Reports

   How, why, and when to order copies of your free annual credit report.

[21]Using a Credit Card

   It helps to know your rights and responsibilities when you use a credit
   card.

[22]Coping with Debt

   When it comes to dealing with debt, you have options. Find out what you
   can do, and get tips for avoiding scams.

[23]Advance-Fee Loans

   Some advance-fee loan and credit card offers have tell-tale signs that
   can help you avoid getting ripped off.

[24]Credit Repair: How to Help Yourself

   Find out how you can improve your credit and get free or low-cost help.

Housing

   Your home is one of the most expensive purchases you'll ever make, and
   may be one of your most valuable assets. Learn how to comparison shop
   for a mortgage, what to do if you can't make your payments, and what to
   consider if you're thinking about tapping into your home equity.

[25]Shopping for a Mortgage

   Shopping and negotiating for a home loan or mortgage -- as you do for
   other major purchases -- may save you thousands of dollars.

[26]When Paying the Mortgage is a Struggle

   If you're having trouble paying your mortgage, all is not lost. There
   is legitimate help to help you save your home.

[27]Home Equity Loans and Credit Lines

   Is a home equity loan or line of credit right for you? Read about
   abusive lending practices, how to avoid them, and how to save your
   home.

[28]Reverse Mortgages

   Reverse mortgages let you cash in on the equity in your home: these
   mortgages can have serious implications.

Work & School

   Whether you're looking for a job, a business to run, or continuing your
   education, this information can help you save time and money, and avoid
   potential rip-offs.

[29]Finding a Job

   Not all job placement services are legitimate. Here are tips to help
   you recognize those that aren't.

[30]Employment Background Checks

   Your application for a job means an employer can check your credit
   report. Here are some things to know.

[31]Work-at-Home Businesses

   Many work-at-home opportunities are promoted by scam artists. If you
   pay in, it's likely that you will spend more than you can earn.

[32]Business Opportunity Scams

   Looking to earn extra income? Before you spend money on a new
   opportunity, learn about your rights under the FTC's Business
   Opportunity Rule, and questions to ask that can help you avoid a
   rip-off.

[33]Student Loans

   Some companies use deceptive claims or business practices to get your
   student loan business.

Automobiles

   Owning a car can be an expensive proposition. Learn how to comparison
   shop, negotiate the best deal, what to do if you can't make your
   payments, and how to avoid auto repair rip-offs.

[34]Buying a New Car

   Get tips about pricing terms, financing options, trade-ins, and service
   contracts.

[35]Buying a Used Car

   The Buyers Guide is required on all used cars sold by dealers. Read
   about payment options, private sales, warranties, service contracts and
   spoken promises.

[36]Understanding Vehicle Financing

   Before you lease or financing a new or used vehicle, learn more about
   your options and what to expect at the dealership.

[37]Vehicle Repossession

   Here's "must know" information about when and how your car can be
   repossessed.

[38]Auto Repair Basics

   Take the scare out of auto repair with these tips about how your
   vehicle works, how to identify common problems, and how to select a
   good mechanic.

